{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-post-template-js","path":"/posts/5508","webpackCompilationHash":"","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"id":"5ca31378-f638-52e7-be43-0a6a9345f407","html":"<h2 id=\"이온-주입에-대한-dopant-diffusion-ion-implantation\"><a href=\"#%EC%9D%B4%EC%98%A8-%EC%A3%BC%EC%9E%85%EC%97%90-%EB%8C%80%ED%95%9C-dopant-diffusion-ion-implantation\" aria-label=\"이온 주입에 대한 dopant diffusion ion implantation permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>이온 주입에 대한 Dopant diffusion, ion implantation</h2>\n<h3 id=\"diffusion-vs-ion-implantation\"><a href=\"#diffusion-vs-ion-implantation\" aria-label=\"diffusion vs ion implantation permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Diffusion Vs Ion Implantation</h3>\n<p>확산과 이온주입은 불순물 원자를 반도체 안에 주입할 때 쓰는 기법</p>\n<p><img src=\"/media/POST/5508/0.jpg\" alt=\"Aspect ratio\"></p>\n<p>Low-temperature technique으로 고 에너지 이온의 빛을 반도체에 비추면 격자\u000b원자와 이온들의 충돌이 일어나 결정구조의 \u000b왜곡을 초래한다. 그 후, 왜곡을 해결하기 위해 annealing단계를 거친다.(Ion implantation setup with mass separator)</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\"> ※ annealing : 고온으로 장시간 유지시킨 후 서서히 냉각하는 열처리</code></pre></div>\n<h3 id=\"what-is-ion-diffusion\"><a href=\"#what-is-ion-diffusion\" aria-label=\"what is ion diffusion permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>What is Ion Diffusion?</h3>\n<p>High-temperature technique으로 원자 수준에서 불순물의 이동을 고려한 것으로, 농도의 기울기(gradient) 때문에 발생한다. (Three main sources of dopants: gaseous, liquid, and solids)</p>\n<h4 id=\"1-gaseous-sources\"><a href=\"#1-gaseous-sources\" aria-label=\"1 gaseous sources permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>1. Gaseous sources</h4>\n<p>안정적이고 편의성 때문에 가장 널리 사용되는 기법이다.(<span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math><semantics><mrow><mi>B</mi><msub><mi>F</mi><mn>3</mn></msub><mo separator=\"true\">,</mo><mi>P</mi><msub><mi>H</mi><mn>3</mn></msub><mo separator=\"true\">,</mo><msub><mi>A</mi><mi>s</mi></msub><msub><mi>H</mi><mn>3</mn></msub></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">BF_{3}, PH_{3}, A_{s}H_{3}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.8777699999999999em;vertical-align:-0.19444em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\" style=\"margin-right:0.05017em;\">B</span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathdefault\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">F</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.30110799999999993em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.5500000000000003em;margin-left:-0.13889em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\">3</span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.15em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mpunct\">,</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.16666666666666666em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">P</span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathdefault\" style=\"margin-right:0.08125em;\">H</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.30110799999999993em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.5500000000000003em;margin-left:-0.08125em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\">3</span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.15em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mpunct\">,</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.16666666666666666em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathdefault\">A</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.151392em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.5500000000000003em;margin-left:0em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathdefault mtight\">s</span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.15em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathdefault\" style=\"margin-right:0.08125em;\">H</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.30110799999999993em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.5500000000000003em;margin-left:-0.08125em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\">3</span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.15em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span>)불순물 산화물(dopant oxide)의 결과로서 웨이퍼(wafer) 표면의 산소와 반응 후, 표면에 걸쳐 균일한 불순물 농도를 형성하고 실리콘 안으로 확산한다.</p>\n<h4 id=\"2-liquid-sources\"><a href=\"#2-liquid-sources\" aria-label=\"2 liquid sources permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>2. Liquid sources</h4>\n<p>Bubblers와 Spin on dopant 두 형태로 이용할 수 있다. Bubblers는 액체를 산소와 반응시킨 후 웨이퍼 표면상에 불순물 산화물을 형성하여 수증기로 바꾼다.</p>\n<h4 id=\"3-solid-sources\"><a href=\"#3-solid-sources\" aria-label=\"3 solid sources permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>3. Solid sources</h4>\n<p>ablet or granular form과 disc or wafer form이 있다. Boron nitride(BN) disc는 750~1100도로 산화되는 가장 일반적인 solid source이다.</p>\n<p><img src=\"/media/POST/5508/1.jpg\" alt=\"Aspect ratio\"></p>\n<ul>\n<li>The solute appears to move smoothly and deterministically from high-concentration areas to low-concentration areas.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"what-is-the-difference-between-diffusion-and-ion-implantation\"><a href=\"#what-is-the-difference-between-diffusion-and-ion-implantation\" aria-label=\"what is the difference between diffusion and ion implantation permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>What is the difference between Diffusion and Ion Implantation?</h3>\n<p><img src=\"/media/POST/5508/2.jpg\" alt=\"Aspect ratio\"></p>\n<p>(참고 : <a href=\"https://www.differencebetween.com/difference-between-diffusion-and-vs-ion-implantation/\">https://www.differencebetween.com/difference-between-diffusion-and-vs-ion-implantation/</a>)</p>\n<h2 id=\"이온-주입에-대한-dopant-확산-simulator\"><a href=\"#%EC%9D%B4%EC%98%A8-%EC%A3%BC%EC%9E%85%EC%97%90-%EB%8C%80%ED%95%9C-dopant-%ED%99%95%EC%82%B0-simulator\" aria-label=\"이온 주입에 대한 dopant 확산 simulator permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>이온 주입에 대한 Dopant 확산 simulator</h2>\n<h3 id=\"dopant-diffusion-simulator\"><a href=\"#dopant-diffusion-simulator\" aria-label=\"dopant diffusion simulator permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Dopant diffusion simulator</h3>\n<p>Dopant diffusion simulator는 실리콘 기판 내부의 As이온이 확산되는 현상을, 파라미터로 받은 dose, energy, temp, duration 값으로 계산해주는 시뮬레이터이다.</p>\n<p><img src=\"/media/POST/5508/3.jpg\" alt=\"Aspect ratio\"></p>\n<p>[Fig. 1. Arsenic Implantation, Dose split, Energy=80keV]</p>\n<ul>\n<li>scatter : Magnetic sector SIMS</li>\n<li>Fig. 1은 As이온의 농도를 <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math><semantics><mrow><mn>1</mn><msup><mi>e</mi><mn>15</mn></msup><mi>c</mi><msup><mi>m</mi><mrow><mo>−</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">1e^{15}cm^{-2}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.8141079999999999em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">1</span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathdefault\">e</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.8141079999999999em;\"><span style=\"top:-3.063em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\">1</span><span class=\"mord mtight\">5</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\">c</span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathdefault\">m</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.8141079999999999em;\"><span style=\"top:-3.063em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\">−</span><span class=\"mord mtight\">2</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span>,<span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math><semantics><mrow><mn>1</mn><msup><mi>e</mi><mn>14</mn></msup><mi>c</mi><msup><mi>m</mi><mrow><mo>−</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">1e^{14}cm^{-2}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.8141079999999999em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">1</span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathdefault\">e</span><span class=\"m